Introduction

FANATICS was a six-member Korean girl group under FENT. The final lineup consisted of Doi, Chiayi, Via, Yoonhye, Rayeon, and Doah. FANATICS debuted on August 6, 2019, with the mini-album "THE SIX".

On April 12, 2020, it was announced that two new members, Rayeon and Via, would be joining the group and that during their next promotions, Yoonhye and Chaelin would be taking a break from group activities. Their second mini-album "PLUS TWO" was released on May 4, 2020.

FANATICS released their first digital single "Starry Night" on May 10, 2021, but only Chiayi, Chaelin, Rayeon, and Doah participated in this comeback. On July 7, 2021, it was revealed that Chiayi, Rayeon, and Doah would be contestants on the reality survival show Girls Planet 999. Rayeon finished 23rd in K-Group and was eliminated in episode five, while Chiayi and Doah were eliminated in episode eight and finished 16th in C-Group and 10th in K-Group, respectively. On September 24, 2021, Sika announced her departure from the group.

In March 2022, Chaelin's name was removed from the description of FANATICS' official YouTube, and her playlist was deleted, leading fans to believe she had left the group. In October 2022, FANATICS' official Instagram and Twitter accounts were deactivated, with Doah also removing FENT from her social media. Despite this, on November 22, 2022, in an interview with Oninews - X Super Idol in Taiwan, Chiayi, and Doi stated that the group had not disbanded and that all six members were preparing for a comeback.

In October of 2024, after three years of the group's inactivity, Via confirmed that FANATICS had disbanded in reply to a fan's comment on her Instagram.
